Algorithm to Count Vowels in a String
1.Start.
2.Input the string str from the user.
3.Initialize count = 0.
4.Convert the string to lowercase for uniformity.
5.Iterate through each character in str:
6.If the character is a vowel ('a','e','i','o','u'), increment count by 1.
7.Print the value of count(total number of vowels).
8.Stop.

PSEUDOCODE:
START
    INPUT str
    count ← 0
    str ← TO_LOWERCASE(str)
    FOR each character ch IN str DO
        IF ch IN ['a', 'e', 'i', 'o', 'u'] THEN
            count ← count + 1
        ENDIF
    ENDFOR
    PRINT count
END

FLOWCHART:
A[Start] --> B[Input str]
    B --> C[Set count = 0]
    C --> D[Convert str to lowercase]
    D --> E[Set i = 0]
    E --> F{Is i < length(str)?}
    F -->|Yes| G{Is str[i] a vowel?}
    G -->|Yes| H[Increment count]
    G -->|No| I[Increment i by 1]
    H --> I
    I --> F
    F -->|No| J[Print count]
    J --> K[Stop]
